Thanks for posting the info, Frank. 
Ive had a play with the MK484 a while ago. It seems very quiet compared to superhet chips, but havent connected a sweep waveform to it.
JEFF 


--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot;purplespacefriend&quot; &lt;purplealiengirl@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt;  It&#39;s in my folder here, I just uploaded it. It worked as a radio, and the audio was really clean. Don&#39;t foget you have to tweak the antenna turns, and positon on the ferrite core to get optimimum results. If you do a google on the MK484, there&#39;s some source of kits for this radio.
&gt; 
&gt;  Joe--I foget his last name--that make&#39;s Joe&#39;s Box, had a version with this chip for AM reception. 
