&gt; --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot;Jeff&quot; &lt;vortex6066@&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Hi Frank,
&gt; &gt; Have you posted the schematic of the TRF circuit? I may have missed this if so. Would be interested to see it. Presume you used the MK484 TRF chip?
&gt; &gt; Incidentally, I heard comment a while ago that the Minibox uses the MK484 chip.
&gt; &gt; JEFF
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Frank Sumption &lt;purplealiengirl@&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt;  If all this EVP stuff is imagination, how come I don&#39;t hear squat for ghost
&gt; &gt; &gt; voices in the audio from the TRF radios? The audio is loud and clear, and
&gt; &gt; &gt; broadcast fragments easily decernable, but few, if any ghost voices. I
&gt; &gt; &gt; thought I got some with a single tuner, but with the double tuner--nothin&#39;!
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt;  I have to wonder if the down conversion process in the standard radio
&gt; &gt; &gt; design is part of the box EVP. In super hetrodyne radios, the original RF
&gt; &gt; &gt; signal is converted to a lower fixed frequency, usually 455khz. So just
&gt; &gt; &gt; providing the raw audio seems to be only part of the box functions, the
&gt; &gt; &gt; other tuned circuits must play a parts--the IF transformers being tuned
&gt; &gt; &gt; circuits, plus the antenna, and the oscillator. Somethin&#39; th think about!
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt;  I tried an LA1135 chip this morning, same as the car tuners use, and it
&gt; &gt; &gt; sounds like a car tuner--so it&#39;s back to the LM3820.
&gt; &gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; &gt; F-S
